      "isOptional": false
    },
    {
      "slug": "soaking-trough",
      "isOptional": false
    }
  ],
  "glossaryTerms": [
    {
      "slug": "slath",
      "term": "Slath",
      "definition": "The central crossed-stake structure of the basket base; in an oval basket, more stakes run along the long axis than the short axis."
    },
    {
      "slug": "stake-and-strand",
      "term": "Stake-and-strand",
      "definition": "Willow-basket weave structure: vertical stakes form the skeleton; weavers pass between them."
    },
    {
      "slug": "pairing",
      "term": "Pairing",
      "definition": "Two-weaver alternating weave; the standard body weave for the cat basket sides."
    },
    {
      "slug": "upset",
      "term": "Upset",
      "definition": "The first rows of weaving above the base that lock the stakes upright and set the basket-side angle."
    },
    {
      "slug": "buff-willow",
      "term": "Buff willow",
      "definition": "Boiled and stripped willow; golden-brown, strong, and consistent. The standard basketry material."
    },
    {
      "slug": "bye-stake",
      "term": "Bye-stake",
      "definition": "A short stake added beside each main side stake after upsetting, doubling the upright density for the main weave."
    },
    {
      "slug": "border",
      "term": "Border",
      "definition": "The finishing technique that bends down the stake tips to form the basket rim."
    },
    {
      "slug": "three-rod-border",
      "term": "Three-rod border",
      "definition": "A plaited border where groups of three stakes are woven around the remaining uprights to form a strong decorative rim."
    }
  ],
  "techniqueSlugs": [],
  "criticalTechniques": [],
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A cat basket is 45 cm long, 35 cm wide, and 20 cm tall at the sides, with a slight inward lean at the rim. The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "slath",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "slath"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " base is oval: more stakes along the long axis than the short. The sides are woven in "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "pairing",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "pairing"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " in "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "buff willow",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "buff-willow"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " with "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "bye-stakes",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "bye-stake"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " added after the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "upset",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "upset"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "three-rod border",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "three-rod-border"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " forms the rim. The intermediate challenge is maintaining the oval shape as the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "stake-and-strand",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "stake-and-strand"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " sides grow: oval baskets need consistent stake spacing at the ends and a deliberate inward press at the rim."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "infoPanel",
        "attrs": {
          "tone": "default",
          "title": "Before you start weaving"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "bulletList",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "listItem",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Secateurs are sharp. Close them when setting down; keep fingers clear of the cutting path."
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "listItem",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Dry willow ends are stiff and springy when trimmed. Guard your face when snipping tall stakes."
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "listItem",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Soaking water: do not leave willow soaking for more than 7 days. Stagnant water grows mould on the rods."
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "listItem",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Workspace: low stable seating, knees together as a lap-board for the work-in-progress."
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Materials"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Buff willow: 14 base stakes at 4 foot (120 cm), 4 mm diameter; 30 side stakes at 32 inches (80 cm), 3 to 3.5 mm; 30 bye-stakes at 24 inches (60 cm), 2.5 to 3 mm; pairing weavers (two full bundles of 4 foot rods, 2 to 2.5 mm). Soak heavy base stakes for 2 hours; all other material for 1 hour."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Base"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Build the oval "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "slath",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                        "attrs": {
                          "termSlug": "slath"
                        }
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": 8 base stakes along the long axis, 6 base stakes across the short axis, crossed through the centre. Open the slath with two pairers, working around groups of stakes then opening to individual stakes."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Work "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "pairing",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                        "attrs": {
                          "termSlug": "pairing"
                        }
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " outward, stretching the oval to 45 cm by 35 cm. Rap down every 3 circuits. Continue until the base reaches the target dimensions. Trim base-stake ends flush with the outer weave row."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Staking and upsetting"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Insert side stakes beside each base stake. Prick up all stakes. Work two rows of "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "upset",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                        "attrs": {
                          "termSlug": "upset"
                        }
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " pairing tight to the base. Adjust the stakes to stand with a slight outward lean at this stage; they will be brought inward at the rim."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Insert "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "bye-stakes",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                        "attrs": {
                          "termSlug": "bye-stake"
                        }
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " beside each side stake. Continue pairing around all uprights until the sides reach 18 cm height."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "At 18 cm, begin pressing the top of the stakes inward slightly with each rapping-iron pass. This creates the inward lean that forms the basket rim profile. A cat basket rim should be about 5 cm smaller in diameter than the basket body at its widest point."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Border"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When the sides reach 20 cm, work the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "three-rod border",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "three-rod-border"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " to close the basket. The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "border",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "border"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " seals the stake tips and forms the firm rim that a cat will push against when entering the basket. Damp the stake tips before working the border if they have dried during weaving."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Finishing"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Trim all weaver ends inside the basket with secateurs. Fit a removable cushion inside the basket for the cat. Leave the basket to dry for 48 hours before first use. The buff willow stiffens as it dries and the rim holds its shape."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Variations"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Smaller dog or rabbit basket: reduce the base to 35 cm by 25 cm and the sides to 15 cm."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Low-sided tray version: reduce the sides to 8 cm for a shallow resting tray without enclosing sides."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Foot rail: add a ring of thicker rods (5 mm) around the base perimeter before staking up, to protect the base weave from floor abrasion."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "heading": "What can go wrong",
          "intro": "Common problems and their fixes.",
          "items": [
            {
              "symptom": "Basket narrows too much at the top before the border",
              "cause": "Stakes pushed inward too early and too aggressively",
              "fix": "Begin the inward lean only in the last 5 cm of side height. The lean should be gradual, not a sharp step."
            },
            {
              "symptom": "Oval base becomes round as weaving progresses",
              "cause": "The oval shape not maintained during base pairing",
              "fix": "Pull the long axis of the base gently during pairing to maintain the oval. Check the dimensions every 5 circuits against the target 45 cm by 35 cm."
            },
            {
              "symptom": "Border stakes crack at the kink point",
              "cause": "Stakes too dry when the border was worked",
              "fix": "Soak the top 10 cm of each stake in water for 30 minutes before the border. Do not attempt the border on dry stakes."
            }
          ]
        }
      }
    ]
  }
}